  "text": "Area under this curve (AUC) indicates the accuracy of NPRS-NP for differentiating between the group that improved or remained stable. The value of AUC for the difference of NPRS-NP closer to \"1\" indicates better agreement with the GROC-NP as an external anchor or the gold standard where AUC = 0.5 means that NPRS-NP cannot accurately differentiate between the group that improves and that does not beyond chance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Sensitivity analyses were conducted, with ROC curves and values of AUC determined for the sub-groups which demonstrated small improvement (GROC = 5), medium improvement (GROC = 6) and large improvement (GROC = 7). It was hypothesized that the AUC values would be equal to or more than 0.7 in each instance.",
